&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an organized and detail-oriented &lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;onsite admissions specialist&lt;/span&gt; to join our team. The &lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;onsite admissions specialist&lt;/span&gt; will be responsible for handling patient intake processes, ensuring accuracy and efficiency in all aspects of the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duties:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Manage patient intake procedures and ensure all necessary information is accurately recorded&lt;br&gt;- Coordinate with medical staff to schedule appointments and maintain the appointment calendar&lt;br&gt;- Verify insurance information and communicate coverage details to patients&lt;br&gt;- Answer phone calls and address patient inquiries in a professional and timely manner&lt;br&gt;- Maintain confidentiality and adhere to HIPAA guidelines at all times&lt;br&gt;- Assist in maintaining medical records and updating patient files as needed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Familiarity with medical scheduling software and phone systems&lt;br&gt;- Knowledge of HIPAA regulations and compliance standards&lt;br&gt;- Strong organizational skills with attention to detail&lt;br&gt;- Ability to multitask in a fast-paced environment&lt;br&gt;- Experience as a Medical Receptionist, Dental Receptionist, or similar role is a plus&lt;br&gt;- Front desk experience in an ER or medical facility is beneficial&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position offers the opportunity to work in a dynamic healthcare environment, contributing to the efficient operation of patient intake processes. If you possess the required qualifications and are looking to make a difference in healthcare administration, we encourage you to apply for the Intake Coordinator position.&lt;/p&gt;
