&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Altior Healthcare&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our family of services comprises three distinct mental health treatment programs, including a specialized program for US Veterans. With over 15 unique locations, we manage and support 500+ dedicated employees serving over 300 residential clients daily located across five states: California, Idaho, Maine, New Hampshire, and Texas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paradigm Treatment (West Coast) and Ridge RTC (East Coast) partner together under Altior, united by a shared commitment to providing exceptional mental health care. For over a decade, our core clinical and support teams have worked side-by-side, delivering compassionate, evidence-based treatment that changes lives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the Altior network, you’ll find the stability of an established organization with the heart of a close-knit treatment community where every role matters.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Job Summary&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Mental Health Therapist provides individual, group, and family therapy to adolescents and/or young adults experiencing mental health and behavioral health challenges. This role collaborates with a multidisciplinary clinical team to support patients throughout a structured treatment episode and into successful aftercare. This person will be a weekend only Therapist.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide individual, group, and family therapy to adolescents and/or young adults experiencing anxiety, depression, substance use, and other co-occurring mental and behavioral health conditions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct comprehensive clinical interviews and assessments with patients and parents/guardians.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain therapeutic rapport with each assigned patient throughout a 28–35 day treatment episode.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain thorough, timely, and accurate clinical documentation, including progress notes and clinical observations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Synthesize and communicate relevant clinical information to multidisciplinary team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in and support aftercare and discharge planning, partnering with families and internal/external clinical teams to ensure continuity of care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adhere to ethical standards and all applicable clinical, regulatory, and licensing requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
